    "narrative": "The LawDog lineup for April 25th leans heavily into situational leverage, with **Cal Raleigh** (71.29) standing as our premier play. Facing Liberatore, **Cal Raleigh** benefits from a massive 10% boost due to the SP skill delta and an advantageous 2-hole spot in the order, making him our highest-projected asset for run production. Close behind is **Geraldo Perdomo** (68.05), whose leadoff assignment against the vulnerable M\u00e1rquez (5.26 xERA) provides an elite ceiling for run-scoring potential. **Bryson Stott** (66.12) and **Jonathan Aranda** (65.18) also offer strong returns, as both capitalize on high SP-skill adjustments that compensate for park factors. Despite facing the formidable Gausman, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** remains a core start (64.57), as his base projections and favorable lineup positioning are too valuable to move to the bench even in a sub-optimal matchup.\n\nWe are paying close attention to the Eury P\u00e9rez matchup, where the synergy between wind conditions and slow delivery rates creates unique upside for our speed-oriented assets. **Matt Chapman** (58.72), **Luis Arraez** (55.62), and **Jung Hoo Lee** (52.84) all receive specific bumps for this interaction; specifically, the base-stealing potential against P\u00e9rez is a critical factor in maintaining our scarcity lead in the SB category. **Taylor Ward** represents our most volatile start; while he faces a difficult assignment in Crochet (2.86 xERA), a 16% park adjustment keeps him viable for home run potential. Conversely, **Daulton Varsho** (48.21) remains in the lineup despite a platoon-heavy penalty, edging out the bench options due to his floor in multi-category contributions.\n\nOur toughest roster choice centered on **Wenceel Perez**, who narrowly missed the starting cut with a score of 44.33. While his park and SP-skill metrics were favorable, his suboptimal spot at the bottom of the order and a negative platoon dynamic against Singer ultimately dropped his efficiency below our current starters. **Masyn Winn** was also considered but failed to clear our 40.0 \"Zebras Floor\" due to his high-difficulty matchup against Woo, prompting us to bench him to preserve game caps for higher-leverage nights. We will continue to monitor lineups for **Drew Gilbert**, whose late-order placement and current 44.41 projection suggest he is the next candidate to be swapped if any weather-related risk emerges in the late games.",
